  "summary": {
    "en": "Pathum Wan is one of the fifty districts (khet) of Bangkok, Thailand. It lies just beyond the old city boundary of Khlong Phadung Krung Kasem and was a rural area on the eastern outskirts of the city when royal villas were built there in the late nineteenth century. The district was officially established in 1915, and covers an area of 8.37 square kilometres (3.23 sq mi). A large part of the district area is taken up by the campus of Chulalongkorn University and the green expanses of Lumphini Park and the Royal Bangkok Sports Club. By the turn of the 20th–21st centuries, the district had become known as the modern-day city centre, home to the prominent shopping areas of Siam and Ratchaprasong.",
    "zh": "巴吞旺（Pathum Wan）为曼谷大都会管理局下辖的行政区（เขต）。概述依据英文维基百科该区条目公开摘要。",
    "th": "ปทุมวัน เป็นเขตการปกครองของกรุงเทพมหานคร สรุปภาพรวมอ้างอิงจากบทคัดย่อสาธารณะของวิกิพีเดียภาษาอังกฤษสำหรับเขตนี้"
  },
